CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Want Negro Cheerleaders - Rankin citizens, like Mrs. Janet Hall (arrow) emphasized during this week's "school strike" meetings in her hometown, that Rankin High School does not have Negro cheerleaders, but should have them so that both colored and white students will know that they are going to a truly democratic school. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men, and women, including Janet Hall in center wearing dark suit jacket, gathered in McCrady school auditorium during school board meeting, Rankin
